The paper discusses the use of distributed and Big Data management technologies for the analysis of large datasets of biological sequences, specifically focusing on k-mer counting. This involves the use of frameworks such as Apache Hadoop and Spark, which are commonly used in the areas of data science and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DB (Databases), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper also discusses the biological aspects of the analysis, which could potentially fall under the sub-categories of q-bio.GN (Genomics) and q-bio.QM (Quantitative Methods).
